A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Collie Greenwood; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, a 45-year veteran of the transit industry, Collie Greenwood joined MARTA in
3 July 2019 as Chief of Bus Operations and Urban Planning, was appointed Deputy General
4 Manager of Operations and Urban Planning in 2020, and was named General Manager and
5 Chief Executive Officer by the MARTA Board of Directors in October 2022; and
6 WHEREAS, he is currently leading MARTA's largest expansion and modernization initiative
7 since its founding over 40 years ago, including cutting-edge advancements such as
8 implementing Communications-Based Train Control for improved rail efficiency, expanding
9 zero-emissions bus rapid transit lines, and modernizing fare payment systems to enhance
10 accessibility and customer convenience; and
11 WHEREAS, under Collie Greenwood's leadership, MARTA has earned the Outstanding
12 Public Transportation System Award from the American Public Transportation Association
13 for remarkable leadership, systemwide excellence, and serving as an exemplary role model
14 for other North American transit agencies; and
