15 WHEREAS, prior to joining MARTA, he served as Chief Service Officer for the Toronto
16 Transit Commission, North America's third-largest transit system, where he oversaw bus,
17 subway, streetcar, and accessible transit services as well as station operations and transit
18 security; and
19 WHEREAS, Collie Greenwood is an active member of the American Public Transportation
20 Association, serving on its Executive Committee and Board of Directors as well as Chair of
21 its Standards Development Oversight Council; and
22 WHEREAS, Collie Greenwood continues to drive MARTA's mission forward, leading
23 ambitious infrastructure improvements, modernizing transit services, and positioning the
24 system to meet the growing transportation needs of metro Atlanta.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body recognize and commend Collie Greenwood for his effective,
27 efficient, and dedicated leadership as well as extend best wishes for continued success.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Collie
30 Greenwood.
